{
  "id": "019d340b-0591-73a1-98e9-c1f448923786",
  "content": "# Branch-First Workflow -- Instruction (2026-03-28)\n\nAll development work must happen on feature branches and be merged via pull requests. Never commit directly to master. No exceptions, regardless of change size.\n\nThis applies to: follow-up fixes, test-only changes, single-file edits, documentation, knowledge store syncs in the code repo. Everything.\n\n## Process\n1. Create branch from master (e.g. `fix/flaky-tests`, `feat/42-cold-tier`)\n2. Commit on the branch\n3. Push and create PR via `gh pr create`\n4. Merge to master\n5. Delete the branch\n\n## Why\nFollow-up commits for issue #42 (cold tier test, flaky HNSW fixes) were pushed directly to master without PRs, bypassing review and traceability. Owner reinforced that branch-first is mandatory for all changes.",
